# System Design: Authorised Capital Changes Pipeline

## What It Does (One Line)

An automated, **LangGraph-orchestrated document intelligence pipeline** that ingests a folder of raw Indian MCA corporate filings (Markdown), classifies them, extracts structured data, validates it with strict arithmetic and cross-document rules, and outputs a **traceable capital history table** (JSON + HTML).

---

## Why It Exists

Indian companies filing authorised capital changes (Form SH-7) must submit a bundle of supporting documents — Board Meeting Resolution, EGM/AGM Resolution, MOA Clause V amendment — alongside the SH-7 form. Manually reconciling these across multiple events (e.g. 2018 → 2019 → 2021 → 2024) is error-prone and time-consuming.

**This system automates that reconciliation** with zero human-in-the-loop, flagging discrepancies rather than guessing.

---

