### 7. Logging (`authorised_capital_changes/logging_config.py`)

All pipeline logs are captured simultaneously to the terminal **and** a rotating log file via a single shared `configure_logging()` function.

**Entry points:**

| Entry point | How logging is initialised |
|---|---|
| `run_pipeline.py` | `configure_logging()` called at module level before `main()` |
| `api/main.py` | `configure_logging()` called inside the FastAPI `lifespan` async context manager (runs once at uvicorn startup) |

**Handler stack (both attached to the root logger):**

| Handler | Destination | Format |
|---|---|---|
| `StreamHandler` | Terminal (stdout) | `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS \| LEVEL \| logger.name \| message` |
| `TimedRotatingFileHandler` | `data/logs/pipeline_<YYYY-MM-DD>.log` | Same format |

**Rotation policy:** Rotates at midnight (`when="midnight"`), retains **30 daily files**, UTF-8 encoded.

**Why root logger?** Every node already uses `logging.getLogger(__name__)` — child loggers propagate to the root automatically, so zero changes were needed inside any node or service.

**Sample log output (from a real run):**
```
2026-05-24 07:36:43 | INFO     | root | Logging initialised | file=...pipeline_2026-05-24.log | level=INFO
2026-05-24 07:36:43 | INFO     | ...nodes.ingestion | Ingestion complete | files_read=20 errors=0
2026-05-24 07:36:43 | INFO     | ...nodes.classifier | Classifier complete | classified=20 sh7=4 non_sh7=16 unclassified=0
2026-05-24 07:36:43 | INFO     | ...nodes.relationship_resolver | DocumentGroup built | sh7=SH7_Event1_2018.md event_index=1 board=BoardMeeting_Event1_2018.md egm=EGM_Event1_2018.md moa=MOA_Event1_2018.md unmatched=0
```

**Log file location:**
```
Project/
└── data/
    └── logs/
        ├── pipeline_2026-05-24.log   ← current day
        ├── pipeline_2026-05-23.log   ← yesterday (auto-rotated)
        └── ...                       ← up to 30 days retained
```

