## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **Linear DAG, no parallelism** | Deterministic, reproducible, easy to debug. Each stage's output is the next stage's input. |
| **Rule-based classifier first** | Keeps LLM calls to a minimum; rule-based covers well-named MCA filings reliably. |
| **Blocking vs non-blocking flags** | Arithmetic mismatch → non-blocking (data is still used with flag). Continuity break → blocking (downstream output would be wrong). Cross-doc: majority disagrees → blocking, minority disagrees → non-blocking. |
| **`FieldValue` traceability** | Every output value carries `source_document`, `source_field_machine`, `source_field_human` — so any number in the final table can be traced back to the exact field in the exact file. |
| **`completed_stages` list** | Enables the API status endpoint to report granular progress without database dependency. |
| **No human-in-the-loop** | Explicitly removed. Unresolvable ambiguities are flagged in the report, not paused for review — the system is fully automated. |
| **Centralised logging to file** | `configure_logging()` attaches a `TimedRotatingFileHandler` to the root logger at startup. All node-level `getLogger(__name__)` calls propagate automatically — no per-node changes needed. 30-day retention, daily rotation. |
